	<clause id="cls-5" obligation="normative"><title>Photometric quantity names and symbols</title><p id="_feab181d-5c59-4705-9891-795ed1ed37b4">The names and symbols of photometric quantities listed in <xref target="cls-2"/>, with the spectral luminous efficiency functions listed in <xref target="cls-4"/>, are defined in the following subsections. Similar names and symbols are used for photometric quantities other than those given below.</p>
	<clause id="_photometric_quantities_for_photopic_vision" obligation="normative"><title>Photometric quantities for photopic vision</title><p id="_f9a4b59c-7a03-400d-9b75-1403b636b2fb">The following quantity names and symbols apply for photopic vision (using the <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>V</mi></mstyle><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow></mfenced></math></stem> function):</p>
	<ul id="_c102c504-55e8-4fea-a748-6bfea3d33d5c">
	<li>
	<p id="_897baff6-5820-468a-b5bb-10e0ae5ce6b7">(photopic) luminous flux, <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>Φ</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mtext>v</mtext></mrow></msub></math></stem></p>
