	<clause id="cls-6" obligation="normative"><title>Basic equations relating photometric quantities to radiometric quantities</title><clause id="_general_equation" obligation="normative"><title>General equation</title><p id="_75dd1aab-5673-46d8-ab7c-5fdf7b6f97e2">For a chosen spectral luminous efficiency function <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>V</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></msub><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow></mfenced></math></stem>, the relationship between a photometric quantity, such as luminous flux, <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>Φ</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mtext>v,X</mtext></mrow></msub></math></stem>, and the corresponding radiometric quantity spectral radiant flux, <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>Φ</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mrow><mtext>e</mtext><mi>,</mi><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow></mrow></msub><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow></mfenced></math></stem>, is given by:</p>
	<formula id="eq-2">
	<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>Φ</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mtext>v,X</mtext></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>K</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mtext>cd</mtext></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>V</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></msub><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mtext>cd</mtext></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mrow></mfrac><msub><mrow><mo>∫</mo></mrow><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>Φ</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mrow><mtext>e</mtext><mi>,</mi><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow></mrow></msub><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow></mfenced><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>V</mi></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></msub><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></mrow></mfenced><mtext>d</mtext><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>λ</mi></mstyle></math></stem>
